# Stripe (via Medusa Payment Provider)

> This is NOT the platform's Stripe rule. Here, Stripe is integrated through
> **Medusa's Stripe payment provider** — payments only. Do not port the
> platform's Next.js Embedded Checkout / client-mount / Next.js webhook patterns
> into this repo.

## Scope

- Stripe processes **store payments only**. Catalog, cart, totals, and orders
  are owned by Medusa.
- **Membership/subscriptions are NOT handled here** — they stay on the platform's
  direct-Stripe flow. Medusa v2 has no native subscriptions; do not add them.
- **TWO Stripe accounts** (see `docs/integration-contract.md` → "Stripe accounts"):
  register **two Stripe providers** — **Mundo Espiritual** for physical/digital
  products and **Gedelimbo** for minutes packages. Each has its own keys + webhook
  secret. Select the provider per cart. Never charge products on Gedelimbo or
  minutes on Mundo Espiritual. Customers are inherently separate across accounts;
  identity is keyed by email/`user_external_ids`, not the Stripe customer id.

## Configuration

- Register **both** Stripe providers in `medusa-config.ts` under the Payment
  Module, with distinct provider ids (e.g. `pp_stripe_mundo`, `pp_stripe_gedelimbo`).
- Credentials come from env, never hardcoded: `STRIPE_MUNDO_SECRET_KEY` /
  `STRIPE_MUNDO_WEBHOOK_SECRET` (products) and `STRIPE_GEDELIMBO_SECRET_KEY` /
  `STRIPE_GEDELIMBO_WEBHOOK_SECRET` (minutes). Prefer **restricted API keys**.
- Each account needs its **own Stripe webhook endpoint** pointed at Medusa, each
  verified with its matching webhook secret.

## Payment flow (provider-driven)

The storefront (platform) drives the cart and mounts the **Stripe Payment
Element**; Medusa's provider creates the PaymentIntent and authorizes/captures.

```
storefront: create/refresh cart, set address + shipping method
storefront: initialize payment session (provider "stripe")  -> Medusa creates PaymentIntent -> client_secret
storefront: <PaymentElement> + confirmPayment(client_secret)
storefront: POST /store/carts/{id}/complete                 -> Medusa creates the Order
```

Do not implement custom PaymentIntent creation in this repo outside the provider;
let the Payment Module own the lifecycle.

## On payment success

- Medusa emits `order.placed`. A subscriber notifies the platform with the
  agreed payload (including `stripe_payment_intent_id`) per
  `docs/integration-contract.md`. The platform writes the transaction mirror and
  CRM sync — do NOT write to Supabase/CRM from here.
- Order emails (confirmation, shipped) are sent from Medusa via the Resend
  notification provider.

## Security

- Restricted keys, least privilege; rotate via env, never in code.
- Always verify webhook signatures.
- Treat amounts/totals as Medusa-authoritative; never trust client-sent amounts.